.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-CACHE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.20" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-cache \- Inspect and prune cached image artifacts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose cache [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Inspect reusable imported and prepared image artifacts stored under the cache directory, or prune entries that are no longer needed.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBlist\fR
List cached image artifacts. See hpc\-compose\-cache\-list(1).
.TP
\fBinspect\fR
Inspect cache reuse for the current plan. See hpc\-compose\-cache\-inspect(1).
.TP
\fBprune\fR
Prune cached image artifacts. See hpc\-compose\-cache\-prune(1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose cache list
hpc\-compose cache inspect \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose cache prune \-\-age 7
.fi
